{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848245446,"sessionID":"ses_287349a82ffeLHBLcEuW63BeTo","part":{"id":"prt_d78cdc87e001ZIsUSYN5wKsXmw","messageID":"msg_d78cbfdd9001yqm28Kxdvku5Z3","sessionID":"ses_287349a82ffeLHBLcEuW63BeTo","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-bc4071da4a9a4d29849f21c81d0cdc3a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-008/design.md","content":"# AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-008 — Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 |\n| Module | `pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\n实现基于时间触发的 Sandbox 垃圾回收机制，自动清理过期和空闲的 Sandbox 资源，防止集群资源累积和膨胀。GC 作为后台 goroutine 运行，提供 TTL 强制执行、空闲超时清理、批量处理限制和可配置的时间间隔。\n\n## Design\n\n### Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                        HTTPServer                               │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                SandboxLifecycleManager                   │   │\n│  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌────────────────┐  │   │\n│  │  │  K8sClient  │  │ MemoryStore  │  │ LifecycleConfig│  │   │\n│  │  └─────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └────────────────┘  │   │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                           │                                     │\n│                           │ delegation                          │\n│                           ▼                                     │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                   GarbageCollector                       │   │\n│  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │   │\n│  │  │                   runLoop                          │ │   │\n│  │  │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌────────────────────────────┐  │ │   │\n│  │  │  │ time.Ticker  │──│ runOnce (per cycle)        │  │ │   │\n│  │  │  └──────────────┘  │ ┌────────────────────────┐ │  │ │   │\n│  │  │                    │ │ListExpiredSandboxes    │ │  │ │   │\n│  │  │                    │ │ListInactiveSandboxes   │ │  │ │   │\n│  │  │                    │ │DeleteSandbox (batched) │ │  │ │   │\n│  │  │                    │ └────────────────────────┘ │  │ │   │\n│  │  │                    └────────────────────────────┘  │ │   │\n│  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │   │\n│  │  ┌────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐ │   │\n│  │  │   Start()  │  │    Stop()       │  │ GetStats()   │ │   │\n│  │  └────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └──────────────┘ │   │\n│  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │   │\n│  │  │SetIdleTimeout() ←─ runtime config via idleMu       │ │   │\n│  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │   │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Component Relationships\n\n| Component | Role | Dependencies |\n|-----------|------|--------------|\n| `GarbageCollector` | Periodic cleanup executor | `SandboxLifecycleManager`, `Store` |\n| `SandboxLifecycleManager` | Deletion delegate | `K8sClient`, `Store` |\n| `MemoryStore` | Sandbox metadata storage | `sync.RWMutex` |\n| `runLoop` | Background goroutine ticker loop | `time.Ticker`, `stopCh` |\n| `runOnce` | Single GC cycle logic | `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes` |\n\n### GC Execution Flow\n\n```\nStart() → wg.Add(1) → go runLoop()\n                            │\n                            ├── runOnce(ctx) [immediate]\n                            ├── ticker := NewTicker(interval)\n                            └── for {\n                                  select {\n                                    case <-stopCh: return\n                                    case <-ticker.C: runOnce(ctx)\n                                  }\n                                }\n\nrunOnce(ctx)\n  │\n  ├── ctx, cancel := WithTimeout(ctx, onceTimeout)\n  ├── expired := ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, now, GCBatchSize)\n  ├── inactive := ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, now.Add(-idleTimeout), GCBatchSize)\n  └── for sb in expired + inactive:\n        │\n        ├── DeleteSandbox(ctx, sb.SessionID)\n        │     ├── GetSandboxBySessionID → NotFoundError? return\n        │     ├── K8sClient.Delete(SandboxGVR)\n        │     ├── K8sClient.Delete(SandboxClaimGVR) [if SandboxClaimKind]\n        │     └── Store.DeleteSandboxBySessionID\n        │\n        ├── NotFoundError? continue (ignore)\n        ├── Other error? log + continue\n        └── reason := determineDeletionReason(sb, now, idleTimeout)\n            logger.Info(\"gc deleted sandbox\", ...)\n\nStop() → close(stopCh) → wg.Wait()\n```\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose | Import Path |\n|---------|---------|-------------|\n| `context` | Context with timeout for GC cycles | `context` (stdlib) |\n| `sync` | WaitGroup, RWMutex for concurrency | `sync` (stdlib) |\n| `time` | Duration, Ticker, Now for timing | `time` (stdlib) |\n| `types` | SandboxInfo struct | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` |\n| `apierrors` | IsNotFound error checking | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` |\n| `metav1` | DeleteOptions | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` |\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Core Types\n\n#### GarbageCollector Struct\n\n```go\ntype GarbageCollector struct {\n    manager     *SandboxLifecycleManager  // Deletion delegate\n    interval    time.Duration             // GC cycle interval (default: 2m)\n    onceTimeout time.Duration             // Single cycle timeout (default: 2m)\n    stopCh      chan struct{}             // Graceful shutdown signal\n    wg          sync.WaitGroup            // Goroutine synchronization\n    logger      Logger                    // Structured logging\n    idleTimeout time.Duration             // Idle sandbox threshold (default: 15m)\n    idleMu      sync.RWMutex              // Protects idleTimeout concurrent access\n}\n```\n\n**Field Responsibilities:**\n\n| Field | Type | Purpose |\n|-------|------|---------|\n| `manager` | `*SandboxLifecycleManager` | Delegates `DeleteSandbox` for actual cleanup |\n| `interval` | `time.Duration` | Ticker interval between GC cycles |\n| `onceTimeout` | `time.Duration` | Context timeout for single `runOnce` execution |\n| `stopCh` | `chan struct{}` | Closed on `Stop()` to signal shutdown |\n| `wg` | `sync.WaitGroup` | Ensures goroutine completes before `Stop()` returns |\n| `logger` | `Logger` | Logs GC events (deletions, errors, shutdown) |\n| `idleTimeout` | `time.Duration` | Threshold for inactive sandbox detection |\n| `idleMu` | `sync.RWMutex` | Protects `idleTimeout` for runtime config changes |\n\n#### GarbageCollectorStats Struct\n\n```go\ntype GarbageCollectorStats struct {\n    Interval    time.Duration  // Current GC cycle interval\n    OnceTimeout time.Duration  // Current single-cycle timeout\n    IdleTimeout time.Duration  // Current idle threshold\n}\n```\n\n#### Store Interface Extensions\n\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    // ... existing methods ...\n    ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n}\n```\n\n**New Method Semantics:**\n\n| Method | Input | Output | Purpose |\n|--------|-------|--------|---------|\n| `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `before` timestamp, `limit` | Sandboxes with `ExpiresAt < before` | TTL-based cleanup candidates |\n| `ListInactiveSandboxes` | `before` timestamp, `limit` | Sandboxes with `LastActivity < before` | Idle timeout cleanup candidates |\n\n#### MemoryStore Implementation\n\n```go\ntype MemoryStore struct {\n    mu              sync.RWMutex\n    sandboxes       map[string]*types.SandboxInfo  // sessionID → SandboxInfo\n    expirationIndex map[string]time.Time           // sandboxID → ExpiresAt\n}\n\nfunc (s *MemoryStore) ListExpiredSandboxes(_ context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n    s.mu.RLock()\n    defer s.mu.RUnlock()\n\n    var expired []*types.SandboxInfo\n    for _, sandbox := range s.sandboxes {\n        if sandbox.ExpiresAt.Before(before) {\n            expired = append(expired, sandbox)\n        }\n    }\n\n    // Sort by ExpiresAt ascending (oldest first)\n    sort.Slice(expired, func(i, j int) bool {\n        return expired[i].ExpiresAt.Before(expired[j].ExpiresAt)\n    })\n\n    // Truncate to limit\n    if limit > 0 && len(expired) > limit {\n        expired = expired[:limit]\n    }\n\n    return expired, nil\n}\n\nfunc (s *MemoryStore) ListInactiveSandboxes(_ context.Context, before time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n    s.mu.RLock()\n    defer s.mu.RUnlock()\n\n    var inactive []*types.SandboxInfo\n    for _, sandbox := range s.sandboxes {\n        // Skip sandboxes with zero LastActivity (newly created)\n        if !sandbox.LastActivity.IsZero() && sandbox.LastActivity.Before(before) {\n            inactive = append(inactive, sandbox)\n        }\n    }\n\n    // Sort by LastActivity ascending (most inactive first)\n    sort.Slice(inactive, func(i, j int) bool {\n        return inactive[i].LastActivity.Before(inactive[j].LastActivity)\n    })\n\n    // Truncate to limit\n    if limit > 0 && len(inactive) > limit {\n        inactive = inactive[:limit]\n    }\n\n    return inactive, nil\n}\n```\n\n#### DeletionReason Constants\n\n```go\ntype DeletionReason string\n\nconst (\n    DeletionReasonIdleTimeout        DeletionReason = \"IdleTimeout\"\n    DeletionReasonMaxDurationReached DeletionReason = \"MaxDurationReached\"\n    DeletionReasonUserRequest        DeletionReason = \"UserRequest\"\n)\n```\n\n#### LifecycleConfig GC Fields\n\n```go\ntype LifecycleConfig struct {\n    DefaultTTL          time.Duration  // Default sandbox TTL (8h)\n    DefaultIdleTimeout  time.Duration  // Default idle threshold (15m)\n    DefaultMaxDuration  time.Duration  // Max session duration (8h)\n    GCInterval          time.Duration  // GC cycle interval (2m)\n    GCOnceTimeout       time.Duration  // Single GC cycle timeout (2m)\n    DeletionGracePeriod int64          // K8s deletion grace period (0)\n    DeletionTimeout     time.Duration  // Single deletion timeout (30s)\n}\n```\n\n### Constants\n\n```go\n// pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go\nconst (\n    GCBatchSize               = 16                    // Max sandboxes per GC cycle per category\n    GarbageCollectorInterval  = 2 * time.Minute       // Default GC cycle interval\n    DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute      // Default idle timeout threshold\n    DefaultSandboxTTL         = 8 * time.Hour         // Default sandbox TTL\n    SandboxDeleteTimeout      = 30 * time.Second      // Single deletion timeout\n)\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Constructor\n\n```go\nfunc NewGarbageCollector(\n    manager *SandboxLifecycleManager,\n    interval time.Duration,\n    onceTimeout time.Duration,\n    logger Logger\n) *GarbageCollector\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n- If `interval == 0`, defaults to `GarbageCollectorInterval` (2m)\n- If `onceTimeout == 0`, defaults to `2 * time.Minute`\n- Initializes `idleTimeout` from `manager.config.DefaultIdleTimeout`\n- Creates `stopCh := make(chan struct{})`\n\n### Lifecycle Methods\n\n```go\nfunc (gc *GarbageCollector) Start()\nfunc (gc *GarbageCollector) Stop()\n```\n\n**Start() Contract:**\n- Calls `gc.wg.Add(1)`\n- Launches `go gc.runLoop()`\n- Returns immediately (non-blocking)\n\n**Stop() Contract:**\n- Calls `close(gc.stopCh)` to signal shutdown\n- Calls `gc.wg.Wait()` to block until goroutine completes\n- Returns only after goroutine exits\n\n### Core Logic Methods\n\n```go\nfunc (gc *GarbageCollector) runLoop()\nfunc (gc *GarbageCollector) runOnce(ctx context.Context) error\n```\n\n**runLoop() Contract:**\n- Runs in separate goroutine\n- Executes `runOnce(ctx)` immediately on start\n- Creates `ticker := time.NewTicker(gc.interval)`\n- Loops on `select { <-stopCh, <-ticker.C }`\n- On `stopCh`, logs `\"garbage collector stopped\"` and returns\n- On `ticker.C`, calls `runOnce(context.Background())`\n- Defers `gc.wg.Done()` and `ticker.Stop()`\n\n**runOnce(ctx) Contract:**\n- Creates `ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, gc.onceTimeout)`\n- Returns error if `ListExpiredSandboxes` fails\n- Returns error if `ListInactiveSandboxes` fails\n- Processes at most `GCBatchSize` expired + `GCBatchSize` inactive sandboxes\n- Ignores `NotFoundError` (sandbox already deleted)\n- Logs other errors but continues processing\n- Logs successful deletions with reason\n\n### Runtime Configuration Methods\n\n```go\nfunc (gc *GarbageCollector) SetIdleTimeout(timeout time.Duration)\nfunc (gc *GarbageCollector) getIdleTimeout() time.Duration\nfunc (gc *GarbageCollector) GetStats() GarbageCollectorStats\n```\n\n**SetIdleTimeout(timeout) Contract:**\n- Acquires `gc.idleMu.Lock()`\n- Updates `gc.idleTimeout`\n- Releases mutex\n\n**getIdleTimeout() Contract:**\n- Acquires `gc.idleMu.RLock()`\n- Returns current `gc.idleTimeout`\n- Releases mutex\n\n**GetStats() Contract:**\n- Acquires `gc.idleMu.RLock()`\n- Returns `GarbageCollectorStats{Interval, OnceTimeout, IdleTimeout}`\n- Releases mutex\n\n### Helper Functions\n\n```go\nfunc determineDeletionReason(sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, now time.Time, idleTimeout time.Duration) DeletionReason\n```\n\n**Contract:**\n- If `now.After(sandbox.ExpiresAt)`: return `DeletionReasonMaxDurationReached`\n- If `!sandbox.LastActivity.IsZero()` AND `now.After(sandbox.LastActivity.Add(idleTimeout))`: return `DeletionReasonIdleTimeout`\n- Otherwise: return `DeletionReasonUserRequest`\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Categories\n\n| Error Type | Source | Handling |\n|------------|--------|----------|\n| `NotFoundError` | Store lookup, K8s delete | Silently ignored (already deleted) |\n| `ListExpiredSandboxes` error | Store query | Logged, `runOnce` returns error |\n| `ListInactiveSandboxes` error | Store query | Logged, `runOnce` returns error |\n| `DeleteSandbox` error (non-NotFound) | Lifecycle manager | Logged, continue to next sandbox |\n| K8s API error | Dynamic client | Wrapped in `InternalError` or `ConflictError` |\n\n### Error Flow\n\n```\nrunOnce(ctx)\n  │\n  ├── ListExpiredSandboxes returns error?\n  │     └── logger.Error(\"failed to list expired sandboxes\", \"err\", err)\n  │     └── return err  [stop cycle]\n  │\n  ├── ListInactiveSandboxes returns error?\n  │     └── logger.Error(\"failed to list inactive sandboxes\", \"err\", err)\n  │     └── return err  [stop cycle]\n  │\n  └── for each sandbox in expired + inactive:\n        │\n        ├── DeleteSandbox returns *NotFoundError?\n        │     └── continue  [ignore, already deleted]\n        │\n        ├── DeleteSandbox returns other error?\n        │     └── logger.Error(\"gc delete failed\", \"sessionID\", ..., \"err\", ...)\n        │     └── continue  [process remaining sandboxes]\n        │\n        └── DeleteSandbox succeeds?\n              └── logger.Info(\"gc deleted sandbox\", \"sessionID\", ..., \"sandboxName\", ..., \"reason\", ...)\n```\n\n### Timeout Handling\n\n| Timeout | Default | Purpose | Mechanism |\n|---------|---------|---------|-----------|\n| `onceTimeout` | 2m | Prevent GC cycle from hanging | `context.WithTimeout(ctx, onceTimeout)` |\n| `DeletionTimeout` | 30s | Prevent single deletion from hanging | `context.WithTimeout(ctx, config.DeletionTimeout)` |\n| `interval` | 2m | GC cycle frequency | `time.NewTicker(interval)` |\n\n### Graceful Degradation\n\n- GC continues processing remaining sandboxes even if some deletions fail\n- NotFound errors are treated as success (resource already cleaned)\n- List errors abort the cycle but don't crash the GC\n- GC restarts on next ticker cycle after errors\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests (garbage_collector_test.go)\n\n| Test | Scenario | Verification |\n|------|----------|--------------|\n| `TestNewGarbageCollector` | Constructor with explicit values | Fields set correctly |\n| `TestNewGarbageCollector_DefaultInterval` | Constructor with zero values | Defaults applied |\n| `TestGarbageCollector_StartStop` | Lifecycle management | Start launches goroutine, Stop waits for completion |\n| `TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Expired` | Expired sandbox cleanup | Expired deleted, active remains |\n| `TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Inactive` | Idle timeout cleanup | Inactive deleted, active remains |\n| `TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_Limit` | Batch size enforcement | At most 16 deleted per category |\n| `TestGarbageCollector_runOnce_ContinueOnError` | Error resilience | All sandboxes processed |\n| `TestGarbageCollector_GetStats` | Stats retrieval | Correct values returned |\n| `TestGarbageCollector_ConcurrentRunOnce` | Concurrent safety | No race conditions |\n\n### Test Setup Pattern\n\n```go\nfunc setupTestGC(t *testing.T) (*GarbageCollector, *MemoryStore) {\n    fakeClient := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n    dynamicClient := dynamicfake.NewSimpleDynamicClient(runtime.NewScheme())\n    informerFactory := NewTestInformerFactory(fakeClient)\n\n    k8sClient := &K8sClient{\n        dynamicClient:   dynamicClient,\n        coreClient:      fakeClient,\n        informerFactory: informerFactory,\n    }\n\n    store := NewMemoryStore()\n    logger := &mockLogger{}\n    config := DefaultLifecycleConfig()\n\n    manager := NewSandboxLifecycleManager(k8sClient, store, config, logger)\n    gc := NewGarbageCollector(manager, GarbageCollectorInterval, 2*time.Minute, logger)\n\n    return gc, store\n}\n```\n\n### Mock Logger\n\n```go\ntype mockLogger struct{}\n\nfunc (l *mockLogger) Info(msg string, args ...any) {}\nfunc (l *mockLogger) Error(msg string, args ...any) {}\n```\n\n### Integration Tests (integration_test.go)\n\n| Test | Scenario | Verification |\n|------|----------|--------------|\n| Full GC flow | Create expired sandbox → run GC | Sandbox deleted from store and K8s |\n| Multiple cycles | 20+ expired sandboxes | GC processes across multiple cycles |\n| Lifecycle integration | Server start/stop | GC lifecycle bound to server |\n\n### Test Coverage Goals\n\n| Area | Target Coverage |\n|------|------------------|\n| `garbage_collector.go` | >80% |\n| `store.go` (GC methods) | >80% |\n| `lifecycle.go` (`determineDeletionReason`) | 100% |\n\n### Validation Commands\n\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager -v -run GarbageCollector\ngo test ./pkg/workloadmanager -coverprofile=coverage.out\ngo tool cover -func=coverage.out\ngo vet ./pkg/workloadmanager\ngolangci-lint run ./pkg/workloadmanager\n```\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [x] `GarbageCollector` struct defined with all required fields\n- [x] `NewGarbageCollector` constructor with default fallbacks\n- [x] `Start()` launches background goroutine\n- [x] `Stop()` signals shutdown and waits for completion\n- [x] `runLoop` uses ticker for periodic execution\n- [x] `runOnce` has context timeout protection\n- [x] `ListExpiredSandboxes` queries expired by `ExpiresAt`\n- [x] `ListInactiveSandboxes` queries inactive by `LastActivity`\n- [x] Batch limit (`GCBatchSize=16`) enforced per query\n- [x] NotFound errors silently ignored\n- [x] Deletion errors logged but don't stop cycle\n- [x] `determineDeletionReason` categorizes deletions correctly\n- [x] `SetIdleTimeout` runtime configuration supported\n- [x] `GetStats` returns current configuration\n- [x] `idleMu` protects concurrent `idleTimeout` access\n- [x] Store interface includes GC query methods\n- [x] `MemoryStore` implements GC query methods\n- [x] `LifecycleConfig` includes GC parameters\n- [x] `DefaultLifecycleConfig` provides GC defaults\n- [x] Unit tests cover expired/inactive/batch scenarios\n- [x] Unit tests cover concurrent safety\n- [x] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n- [x] Pass `golangci-lint` with zero issues\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- Q: Should GC metrics be exported to Prometheus?\n  - A: Deferred to future enhancement. Current implementation uses structured logging only.\n\n- Q: How should distributed GC work with multiple workload-manager instances?\n  - A: Deferred. Leader election can be added when HA deployment is required.\n\n- Q: Should `LastActivity` be updated on heartbeat or only on user actions?\n  - A: Updated on user actions (sandbox creation, heartbeat API calls). The heartbeat handler updates `LastActivity`.\n\n## References\n\n- `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go` - Implementation\n- `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go` - Test coverage\n- `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go` - `DeleteSandbox` delegation, `determineDeletionReason`\n- `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go` - `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes`\n- `pkg/workloadmanager/types.go` - Store interface, `DeletionReason` constants\n- `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` - Timeout constants\n- Kubernetes TTL Controller: https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/workloads/controllers/ttlafterfinished/"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/go.mod":[{"range":{"start":{"line":49,"character":49},"end":{"line":49,"character":60}},"severity":2,"source":"go mod tidy","message":"k8s.io/utils should be direct"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/config_test.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":37,"character":14},"end":{"line":37,"character":14}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field WriteTimeout"},{"range":{"start":{"line":38,"character":13},"end":{"line":38,"character":13}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field IdleTimeout"},{"range":{"start":{"line":39,"character":17},"end":{"line":39,"character":17}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field ShutdownTimeout"},{"range":{"start":{"line":40,"character":15},"end":{"line":40,"character":15}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field EnableHealthz"},{"range":{"start":{"line":41,"character":14},"end":{"line":41,"character":14}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field EnableReadyz"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/common/types/sandbox.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":60,"character":40},"end":{"line":60,"character":71}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#omitzero"},"source":"omitzero","message":"Omitempty has no effect on nested struct fields"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/store.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanage